Abubakar Alkali, a Flight Lieutenant of the Nigerian Air Force (NAF) has been identified as one of the officers killed when a military aircraft crashed in Kaduna State.  SaharaReporters gathered that the training aircraft had two pilots on board when the incident occurred on Tuesday evening.  The aircraft, believed to be a Super Mushak, reportedly crashed within the NAF base while on a training mission.  A statement signed by one Alhaji Sule Dauda confirmed Alkali as one of the pilots onboard the ill-fated aircraft. See Also






